<div class="note-source" id="TSJN-01-04-0574-sn"><p><abbr title="fade=[ on ] fadespeed=[0.1] windowlock=[on] cssbody=[ boxover ] header=[]  body=[ recipient's copy ]">RC</abbr> (<span class="ref-rep" title="fade=[ on ] fadespeed=[0.1] windowlock=[on] cssbody=[ boxover ] header=[]  body=[ Library of Virginia, Richmond ]">Vi</span>); addressed and endorsed. Enclosures: Copy of a Plan for the Quartermasters Department, printed above under 1 Jan. 1781; the copy of the prices established in specie and the return of the assistant deputy quartermasters have not been located.</p>
<p>See <a href="default.xqy?keys=TSJN-print-01-04-02-0629" class="document">TJ to Claiborne, 3 Feb.</a>; <a href="default.xqy?keys=TSJN-print-01-04-02-0676" class="document">Claiborne to TJ, 7 Feb.</a>, and <a href="default.xqy?keys=TSJN-print-01-04-02-0677" class="document">TJs answer, 7 Feb.</a> On 5 Feb. Claiborne informed Timothy Pickering that he had accepted the post of deputy quartermaster for Virginia and enclosed a Copy of the Arrangement for this state made by Colo. Carrington and myself, and approved of by the Executive (<span class="ref-rep" title="fade=[ on ] fadespeed=[0.1] windowlock=[on] cssbody=[ boxover ] header=[]  body=[ The National Archives ]">DNA</span>: <abbr title="fade=[ on ] fadespeed=[0.1] windowlock=[on] cssbody=[ boxover ] header=[]  body=[ Record Group (designates the location of documents in the National Archives) ]">RG</abbr> 93).</p></div>
